						               													<description>A card game for 2-4 players based on the cult classic science fiction movie Blade Runner.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;There are 4 available Blade Runners (Deckard, Bryant, Holden, Gaff) with each player starting as one of them.  Each operative has a unique special ability.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Players share a common deck which has seven types of cards, each of which has a special ability and a rank: &amp;#10;Replicant        Take top card of discard&amp;#10;Location               Draw 3 cards and keep 1&amp;#10;Test            Look at opponents hand&amp;#10;Combat            Opponent must discard 1 random card&amp;#10;Transport        Draw 2 cards&amp;#10;Investigation        Look at next 7 cards in deck&amp;#10;Complications        Steal 1 random card from opponent&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Players take turns with each turn comprising four phases:&amp;#10;&amp;#10;1.  Search Phase &amp;#10;-   Draw 2 Cards.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;2.  Action Phase &amp;#10;-   You may play 1 card for its special ability.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;3.  Assignment Phase &amp;#10;-   Complete an Assignment - discard at least 1 of each card type. &amp;#10;-   Threat Rule: An assignment play must contain 1 or 2 combat cards with a combined rank value that is equal to or greater than that of the rank value of the Replicant.  &amp;#10;-   Search Rule: The combined ranks of the Investigation and Test cards played must be equal to or greater than 10. &amp;#10;-   Travel Rule: The ranks of the Location and Travel cards must be within 2 of each other.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;4.  Debriefing Phase &amp;#10;-   Max hand size is 8 cards. Discard excess cards.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The first player to complete 3 assignments is the winner.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
